HEADWORD: Sadda
<hw>Sad"da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>sad-dar</ets> the hundred gates or ways; <ets>sad</ets> a hundred +
<ets>dar</ets> door, way.]</ety> <def>A work in the Persian tongue,
being a summary of the Zend-Avesta, or sacred books.</def>⟦br⟧
